claim.claim-text:
22. A method for providing an electrochemical cell comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a positive electrode; 
b) mixing a carbonaceous material with a second anode material selected from the group consisting of a lithiated transition mixed metal oxide, a lithiated transition metal oxide and a lithiated transition metal sulfide; 
c) providing a negative electrode by contacting the mixed carbonaceous material and the second anode material to an anode current collector; and 
d) activating the positive electrode and the negative electrode with an electrolyte.
